page.title: 04ECOLOGY IN ASTON-J-M (2)
page.content: {Fungi}found are:brackets on oak trees, horse mushrooms in the fields,giant puffballs and ink caps.Kingfishers are to be seen over the river Weaver and the many varieties of{common birds including blackbird,sparrow,blue-tit, great tit,starling,pigeon,sea gull, lapwing,rook,crow,robin and wren. {Foxes' earths}are present and frequent and at least one large{badgers sett}is to be found in a wood.Water vole holes are visible in the banks of the river Weaver and the canal.The canal and river support many types of{fish}such as perch,roach,bream and gudgeon.
